$$30x^3-8x^2+20x=10x(3x^2-8x+2)$$Now, we have to find factors of $3x^2-8x+2$ that multiply to $3x^2$. In other words, we need a pair of factors that multiply to $3x^2$ and add to $-8x$ to get the middle term. After some trial and error, we find that $3x$ and $x$ will work, since $3x(x)-x(3x)=-8x$.
$$3x^2-8x+2=3x(x)-x(3x)+(2)$$Now that we have the right factors, we can think of this as $$(x-2)(3x)=3x(x)-2x$$Collecting like terms and simplifying, we get \begin{align*}
10x(3x^2-8x+2) &=10x((x-2)(3x))\\
&=10x^2(3x)-10x(x)(2)\\
&=30x^3-20x^2\\
&=\boxed{30x^3-8x^2+20x}
\end{align*}
